    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nfoldenable is true by default, this makes code folded when open file. This make very strangle. Maybe we should set it to false by default.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nfoldenable is set to false by default.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Defaults are changed when there is a clear case to be made for doing so. Do most users want folds or not? Don't see this in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/21342 , maybe @echasnovski can comment",
