            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Defaults are changed when there is a clear case to be made for doing so. Do most users want folds or not? Don't see this in #21342 , maybe @echasnovski can comment\r\n\r\nThe [raw data](https://gist.github.com/echasnovski/fa70dc75c475369747d2a485a13303fb#file-neovim-survey-summary_02_all-csv) (which can be queried in the top search bar) shows that default value of `foldenable=true` had about 86% of respondents (196 out of 227). My guess would be that this describes two sets of people: who actually use folds and who don't know about folds (and did not encounter problems with the default `foldmethod=manual` which use about 59% of respondents).\r\n\r\nI personally love using folds with `foldmethod=indent` (which is quite universal and works in at least 90% of cases).",
